    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "Lynne Ramsay's 'Die My Love'",
      "note": "MUBI, going wide",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Die My Love",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Impressionistic, experiential film about postpartum depression, with Jennifer Lawrence and Robert Pattinson as a couple who move from New York to Montana. Amanda calls it one of her favorites of the year, catered directly to her; Rob loved it while wanting to throw up throughout. All three rate Lawrence's feral, largely naked performance the best of her career, though they doubt the film is a big enough awards play for her to get in. Martin Scorsese read the source novel and suggested Lawrence for the part; she was pregnant during filming."
        }
      ]
    }
